article.headline: Cleveland St. 74, Ill.-Chicago 63
article.story: CHICAGO -- Trevon Harmon put in 17 points and led four Cleveland State players in double-digit scoring as part of the Vikings' 74-63 victory over Illinois-Chicago on Thursday night. The Vikings (11-12, 7-4 Horizon) led the entire game, going into halftime up 44-29 and never looking back. It was their fourth straight win. Norris Cole grabbed a double-double by scoring 13 points and making 10 assists. D'Aundray Brown finished with 15 points while Jeremy Montgomery added 13. Jeremy Buttell and Zavion Neely led the Flames (5-17, 1-11) with 17 points each. Buttell also pulled down 10 rebounds.
